Deploy Models

To deploy a model, open it, click Deploy Model, and then complete the following steps.

Select a Target Prediction Definition or Model
Select Whether to Connect to a Salesforce Object
Map Model Variables
Configure Projected Predictions
Configure Segmentation Filters
Select Actionable Variables for Suggested Improvements
Customize Prediction Text
Review Your Selections and Deploy the Model

Before you deploy a model, consider reviewing Model Metrics and setting the threshold level in Threshold Evaluation for Binary Classification Use Cases. If automated prediction writeback is desired, read deployment requirements.

To deploy a model, choose how you want to deploy it: to a new prediction definition, to an existing prediction definition, or to replace an existing model. Decide which Salesforce object, if any, you want to associate with the prediction. Define the mapping between variables in the model and fields in the Salesforce object or columns in the supplemental dataset.
